<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2345</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-24">September 24, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Australian Minister called at his request. I said that there was no
                            change in the exploratory talks with Japan, and that the matter looked
                            less favorable than it had for some time. The Minister was naturally
                            very much interested in information on this subject.</p>
                        <p>Some minor references to matters of no particular consequence were
                            made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>